# Genetic Regulation of Circadian Rhythms

## Introduction

The molecular mechanisms controlling circadian rhythms involve transcription-translation feedback loops (Takahashi 2020). Laboratory experiments identified key regulatory proteins using CRISPR-Cas9 gene editing (n=180 cell lines).

## Experimental Design

Methodology followed established protocols for cell culture and genetic manipulation (Roberts & Green 2021, doi.org/10.9012/circadian). Measurements captured bioluminescence rhythms over 120-hour periods with 30-minute temporal resolution.

## Results

Statistical analysis demonstrates that clock gene mutations alter period length significantly (Δt=2.1±0.3 hr, p<0.001). Quantitative data shows phase-dependent protein expression (Figure 3) matching computational models (Wang 2019).

The findings indicate that post-translational modifications regulate stability (Peterson et al. 2022, https://example.com/clock-genes). Replication studies confirm robust effects across cell types (Miller 2020, arxiv.org/abs/2012.56789).



